efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n) per gather, O(maxRow) per scatter
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a segment tree to track remaining seats per row. gather finds the first row with enough contiguous seats via segment tree max query. scatter checks total seats in range via segment tree sum query and then greedily fills from lowest rows. Segment tree with lazy propagation ensures efficient range updates and queries.

